JOHANNESBURG - Penalties are in place to deal with employers who contravene the national minimum wage once it is implemented. National Minimum Wage Bill is expected to be implemented from 1 May. READ: Numsa threatens court action over 'insulting' national minimum wage Under the new law, employers will have to pay their staff a minimum wage of R20 an hour. The introduction of a national minimum wage is expected to increase the earnings of more than six million working South Africans.
	
